In summary, I identified four segments (1, 2, and 7) where Q7 applied. These segments downplayed the risk or made definitive negation-based statements without offering any additional reassurance. The remaining segments either lacked the specific phrasing targeted by Q7 or stated facts without such implied downplaying. I've categorized them as not meeting the bare negation criteria. Moving forward, for the segments that responded "no", I would move onto the Q8 assessment.
